verbs.description: wirepull (third-person singular simple present wirepulls, present participle wirepulling, simple past and past participle wirepulled)

entries.meaning: (transitive, intransitive) To exert an influence on (others) that is felt but not seen.
examples: These basic provisions of the 1954 Geneva agreements on Vietnam do not allow the United States to wirepull its lackeys to rig up the so-called Republic of Vietnam.
